  <!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

<FAQs
title="Frequently Asked Questions"
items={[
  {
    title: 'What is PPC, and how does it work?',
    description:
      'PPC (Pay-Per-Click) is an online advertising model where you pay each time someone clicks on your ad. It allows you to bid for ad placement in search engine results or on websites, ensuring your ads reach your target audience.',
    icon: 'tabler:chevrons-right',
  },
  {
    title: 'How much does PPC advertising cost?',
    description:
      'The cost of PPC advertising varies depending on factors like industry, competition, and targeting. You set a budget, and you only pay when someone clicks on your ad, making it a cost-effective way to drive traffic.',
    icon: 'tabler:chevrons-right',
  },
  {
    title: 'How long does it take to see results from PPC?',
    description:
      'PPC campaigns can deliver immediate results, as your ads start appearing as soon as they’re live. However, optimizing campaigns for maximum ROI may take a few weeks as we analyze data and refine strategies.',
    icon: 'tabler:chevrons-right',
  },
  {
    title: 'Do you manage PPC campaigns for all platforms?',
    description:
      'Yes, we manage PPC campaigns across platforms like Google Ads, Bing Ads, and social media channels like Facebook and LinkedIn. We tailor campaigns to your goals and target audience.',
    icon: 'tabler:chevrons-right',
  },
]}
>
